'''Adrian Michael Berry, 4th Viscount Camrose''' (15 June 1937 – 18 April 2016)<ref name="Telegraphobit">
{{cite web | url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/obituaries/2016/04/19/viscount-camrose--obituary/
|title= Viscount Camrose |accessdate=19 April 2016}}</ref> was a British [[hereditary peer]], journalist, and writer.

==Biography==
Berry was born in 1937, the elder son of [[Michael Berry, Baron Hartwell|Michael Berry]], who was later created Lord Hartwell, and disclaimed the family title of [[Viscount Camrose]], by his marriage to Lady [[Pamela Smith]], the daughter of [[F. E. Smith, 1st Earl of Birkenhead|F.E. Smith]].<ref name="Telegraphobit"/> Adrian Berry was educated at [[Eton College|Eton]] and [[Christ Church, Oxford]]. 

From 1977 until 1996, he was the science correspondent of ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]''. On stepping down from that position he became the paper's Consulting Editor (Science).<ref name="Telegraphobit"/> He was a [[FRGS#Fellowship|Fellow of the Royal Geographical Society]], a [[Royal Astronomical Society#Fellowship|Fellow of the Royal Astronomical Society]], and a [[British Interplanetary Society|Fellow of the British Interplanetary Society]].

==Marriage and family==
In 1967, Berry married Marina Beatrice Sulzberger, daughter of [[Cyrus Leo Sulzberger II|Cyrus Sulzberger]] (a member of the family which owns ''[[The New York Times]]'') and Marina Tatiana Ladas. The couple had two children:<ref>[http://thepeerage.com/p4517.htm#i45168  The Peerage, entry for 4th Viscount Camrose]</ref>

* [[The Honourable|Hon]] Jessica Margaret Berry (born 11 February 1968)
* [[Viscount Camrose|Jonathan William Berry, 5th Viscount Camrose]] (born 26 February 1970)

==Climate change==
In his article published in ''[[The Sunday Telegraph]]'' in 2015, Berry argued that [[climate change]] "has more to do with the violent outbursts of energy that our solar system meets on its eternal passage through the Milky Way" than on the "fashionable theory of climate change caused by carbon dioxide" which "is contradicted by all the geological evidence."<ref name="climate_change_2015">{{citation |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/science/space/nightsky/11356838/The-Night-Sky-February-2015-is-climate-change-caused-by-astronomical-events-beyond-our-control.html |work=The Sunday Telegraph |title=The Night Sky February 2015: Is climate change caused by astronomical events beyond our control? |date=1 February 2015 |accessdate=1 February 2016 }}</ref> Berry served on the advisory committee of the [[Global Warming Policy Foundation]] (GWPF)<ref name="CWPF_2015">{{citation |url=http://www.thegwpf.org/new-chairman-of-gwpf-academic-advisory-council-2/ |title=New chairman of GWPF academic advisory council|date=4 January 2016 |accessdate=1 February 2016 |work=GWPF }}</ref>—a [[think tank]] that promotes [[Climate change denial|climate-change denial]]<ref name="IJ denial">{{citation|first=Ian |last=Johnston |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/environment/climate-change/nigel-lawsons-climatechange-denial-charity-intimidated-environmental-expert-9350069.html |title=Nigel Lawson's climate-change denial charity 'intimidated' environmental expert |work=The Independent |date=11 May 2014 |accessdate=1 February 2016 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140511082724/http://www.independent.co.uk/environment/climate-change/nigel-lawsons-climatechange-denial-charity-intimidated-environmental-expert-9350069.html |archivedate=11 May 2014 }}</ref> and warns against the "extremely damaging and harmful policies" proposed by governments to [[Climate change mitigation|mitigate]] [[human impact on the environment|anthropogenic]] [[global warming]].<ref name=bbcnews>{{cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/8398103.stm | title=Ed Miliband clashes with Lord Lawson on global warming | date=6 December 2009 | work=[[BBC News]] | publisher=[[news.bbc.co.uk]] | accessdate=22 December 2009 }}</ref><ref name=press>{{Cite press release | title=Launched today! | publisher=The Global Warming Policy Foundation | date=23 November 2009 | url=http://www.thegwpf.org/launched-today/ | accessdate=25 May 2014 }}</ref>
<ref name=advisory>{{cite web | url=http://www.thegwpf.org/who-we-are/academic-advisory-council/ | title=Academic Advisory Council | publisher=Global Warming Policy Foundation | accessdate=25 May 2014 }}</ref><ref name=guten>{{cite web | url=http://www.achgut.com/dadgdx/index.php/dadgd/print/0013917 | title=Benny Peiser ist jetzt Direktor der Global Warming Policy Foundation | last=Miersch | first=Michael | work=Die Achse des Guten | publisher=achgut.com | date=23 November 2009 | accessdate=25 November 2009 }}</ref>

