{{Other uses|National Front (disambiguation){{!}}National Front}}
The '''National Front''' (''Fronte Nazionale'', '''FN''') was a [[Neo-fascism|neo-fascist]] [[list of political parties in Italy|political party in Italy]].
It was founded in 1990 by [[Franco Freda]] and adopted a policy against 'racial mixing' and immigration, whilst also opposing [[Zionism]], what it called 'cosmo-politics', and the influence of the [[United States]] and international finance.<ref name="AXT"/> The group published an economic journal ''L'antibancor'',<ref name="AXT"/> as well as ''Rubric'', a members' bulletin.<ref>''Antisemitism World Report 1994'', Institute of Jewish Affairs, 1994, p. 51</ref> It became moribund after the 1995 conviction of Freda and 49 other members of the party under the [[Mario Scelba|Scelba]] Law which banned the refoundation of the [[National Fascist Party]].<ref name="AXT">[http://www.axt.org.uk/antisem/countries/italy/italy.htm Italy December 1999] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120713051015/http://www.axt.org.uk/antisem/countries/italy/italy.htm |date=2012-07-13 }}</ref><ref>F.G.Freda , ''I lupi azzurri. Documenti del Fronte Nazionale'' , Edizioni di Ar, 2001</ref>
